==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Paroccipital
<hw>Par`oc*cip"i*tal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>para-</ets> + <ets>occipital</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>
<def>Situated near or beside the occipital condyle or the occipital
bone; paramastoid; -- applied especially to a process of the skull in
some animals.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Parochial</ent>⟦br⟧
